  Cloud Tools vs Local Tools

In this quick video, I'm going to explain why we primarily use cloud tools (tools that use other people's machines) to create the majority of our AI artwork. Running AI tools locally on your computer does offer some benefits like customization and cost reduction.

However, to have success with local instances of AI on your machine, all of the following need to be true:

  1. You are a highly technical person
  2. Have an expensive and powerful computer
  3. You are running on a PC
  4. You like to fix bugs and workshop errors
  5. You are fine with updating your software by hand on a regular basis

Instead, we want to limit creative friction so you can focus on being creative and having a blast. We want your creative time to feel like play. This course will guide you to the best tools to reduce creative friction.
